#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:419
msgid "Using the Block"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:421
msgid "In the block editor, insert the Big Orange Pardot block from the Widgets category (or search for \"Pardot\")."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:422
msgid "The block inserts with a default set of seven fields (First Name, Last Name, Email, Phone, Company, Job Title, Comments) plus a Submit button. Each field is its own block — you can reorder, delete, or add fields freely using the block editor."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:425
msgid "If connected to Pardot"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:427
msgid "Open the block settings panel. A dropdown lists all form handlers from your Pardot account. Select the handler this form should submit to — the submission URL is set automatically."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:428
msgid "Any fields the handler expects that are not already in your form are added automatically when you select a handler. Review the added fields and adjust labels, types, or widths as needed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:429
msgid "The settings panel shows how many Pardot fields are present in your form. Use the \"Add missing field(s)\" button to insert any remaining expected fields."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:430
msgid "To start fresh from Pardot's field list, click \"Replace all with Pardot fields\". This removes all current fields and rebuilds them from the handler's configuration."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:434
msgid "Until a form handler is configured, the form is hidden from site visitors. Editors viewing the page while logged in will see a notice above a non-submittable preview of the form, so they can review the layout in context before the form goes live."
